File: A sign on a grave reading RIP. Pixabay/Rob van der Meijden JOHANNESBURG - The seven Ndou family members killed in a mass shooting incident on Christmas day in Malamulele in Limpopo will be laid to rest on Saturday. A task team was established to assist the family with funeral arrangements. READ: Case of Limpopo man accused of killing family postponed A suspect was arrested after he handed himself over at Thohoyandou police station. He appeared briefly in Malamulele magistrate's court on Tuesday. It's believed the incident could be linked to a fight over the family home.